cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.RO 

The paper deals with a reinforcement learning problem in continuous state and action spaces, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of functional optimization methods and kernel-based techniques suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem formulation and algorithm design also involve control theory and optimization, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of stochastic optimization and convergence analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
